  "name": "PO/Supplier Return Settings",
  "body": "<p>To provide customisation and more flexibility for the Purchase Order (PO) templates, we have introduced landscape and portrait orientation options for users to tailor their PO displays according to their preferences.<br/><br/> </p>\n<div><strong>Orientation Choices: (Landscape/Portrait)</strong><br/> </div><br/><br/><div>A portrait orientation version is now available in addition to the landscape version for the Purchase Order (PO) template through the new PO/Supplier Return Settings page. Using the global configuration feature, users can now easily switch between landscape and portrait orientations for their POs.</div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Global Configuration: </strong><br/><br/>The new settings page allows users to configure their preferred layout globally. This means that the chosen orientation will apply to all suppliers and POs by default.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div><b>Note</b>: The PO orientation selection Applies globally to all suppliers, excluding those using the \"Matrix\" template</div>\n<h2 id=\"[hardBreak]How-to-Access-and-Configure:\" data-id=\"how-to-access-and-configure\"><br/><strong>How to Access and Configure:</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>Go to Settings &gt;&gt; Purchase Order Setup &gt;&gt; PO/Supplier Return Settings.</strong><br/><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 483px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/8e0fc95cc08f4947a828da1fb9e4c4b2.05T5g00001BUnlXEAT.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\n<p><br/>On PO/Supplier Return Settings page, select the PO orientation from ‘PO Template Configuration drop-down list. <img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"377\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 377px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1eee5887ba7c48da926f5978b58d3ec6.05T5g00001BUnoqEAD.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\nOnce you have selected the orientation, please click on the ‘Save Changes’ at the bottom of the page.\n<h2 id=\"[hardBreak]Template-Settings\" data-id=\"template-settings\"><br/><br/><strong>Template Settings</strong></h2>\n<p>To understand the impact of this update, let's take a glimpse at what your POs could look like in both landscape and portrait orientations</p>\n<p><strong>Landscape Orientation:</strong></p>\n<p>The default landscape orientation maintains the familiar layout, suitable for users accustomed to this traditional view.</p>\n<div><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"553\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 553px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/fce607f7b958439bb58128bba4528706.05T5g00001BUnpKEAT.jpeg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div><br/><strong>Portrait Orientation:</strong><br/><br/>The portrait orientation, on the other hand, optimizes the display for a more vertical arrangement. This is particularly beneficial for users who prefer a condensed view to save page width.</div>\n<p><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"1107\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 1107px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/dba93636236e4df0bf53953f3ddf6083.05T5g00001BUnqDEAT.jpeg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\n<div><b>Note</b>: The Barcode column will not be available in the portrait mode.</div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 data-id=\"po-flat-file-excel-attachment\"><b>PO Flat File Excel Attachment</b></h2>\n<p>Users have the ability to optionally include an Excel document along with the PDF attachment when emailing Purchase Orders to suppliers. The “Flat File” contains Outlet/Company Information, Purchase Order and Product information, giving the supplier the information they need to ingest the document to their external ERP/Platform.<br/> </p>\n<div>This feature is optional and can be configured via <strong>Settings &gt; Purchase Order Setup &gt; PO/Supplier Return Settings &gt; \"Include PO Details via Excel Flat File as Attachment\"</strong></div><br/><br/><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 482px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123341PM.05TJ100000A2qjHMAR.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img><br/><br/><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 482px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at123503PM.05TJ100000A2qjqMAB.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img><br/><br/>Once configured, the flat file will be automatically attached to PO emails sent from both Stock Replenishment and PO Details, and can also be exported directly from the PO Details and PO Items tabs in the Back Office.\n<p> </p>\n<h2 data-id=\"po-master-vs-outlet-information\"><strong>PO Master vs Outlet Information</strong></h2>\n<p>A Purchase Order setting is available to configure whether to display Master or Outlet information on the Purchase Order Template sent to suppliers. This feature gives users the flexibility to choose between displaying global company information (Master) or outlet-specific details (Outlet).</p>\n<ul><li>\n<p><strong>Settings Location:</strong> Settings &gt; Purchase Order Setup &gt; PO/Supplier Return Settings Page</p>\n\t</li><li>\n<p><strong>Setting:</strong> \"Display Master or Outlet Specific Data on Purchase Orders\"</p>\n<ul><li>\n<p>Master Company Data (Default)</p>\n\t\t</li><li>\n<p>Outlet Specific Company Data</p>\n\t\t</li></ul></li></ul><p><br/>The setting determines whether the Company Name, ABN, Address, Contact Details, and Logo shown on POs is sourced from Global Settings (Master) or Outlet Settings (Outlet).</p>\n<img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 482px; width: 900px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/Screenshot20240730at125203PM.05TJ100000A2rdgMAB.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img>",
